# Production-Grade Test Module — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Complete rebuild of the existing test system into a secure, structured, scalable module. The existing [Test](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Test.ts#14-23), [TestAttempt](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/TestAttempt.ts#8-17) models and related APIs will be replaced by new schemas with full separation of concerns.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Breaking Change:** The existing [Test](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Test.ts#14-23) and [TestAttempt](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/TestAttempt.ts#8-17) MongoDB collections and all existing admin/student test API routes will be replaced by new schemas. Any existing test data in the DB will not auto-migrate.

> [!WARNING]
> **Old MCQ text-paste system removed.** The current teacher feature that pastes raw MCQ text will be replaced by structured JSON file uploads. Teachers will need to prepare `questions.json` and `answers.json` files.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Data Layer — New Models

---

#### [MODIFY] [Test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Test.ts)

Replace existing flat schema with a fully structured `ProTest` schema:

```typescript
ProTest {
  title, description, durationMinutes, totalMarks
  batch: ObjectId(Batch)   // filter tests per batch
  subject: ObjectId(Subject) // filter tests per subject
  negativeMarking: number   // e.g. 0.25 per wrong answer
  shuffleQuestions: boolean
  shuffleOptions: boolean
  resultMode: 'instant' | 'manual'
  isPublished: boolean     // admin publishes results manually
  isActive: boolean
  createdBy: ObjectId(User)
  sections: [{ sectionId, title, instructions }]
  questions: [{
    questionId: string    // unique per test, matches answers.json
    sectionId?: string
    type: 'mcq'
    questionText: string
    marks: number
    options: [{ label: 'A'|'B'|'C'|'D', text: string }]
  }]
}
```

#### [NEW] `src/models/TestAnswerKey.ts`

Separate collection — never returned to students:
```typescript
TestAnswerKey {
  testId: ObjectId(ProTest)
  answers: [{
    questionId: string
    correctAnswer: 'A'|'B'|'C'|'D'
    reason: string
    marks: number   // per-question marks for negative marking calc
  }]
}
```

#### [MODIFY] [TestAttempt.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/TestAttempt.ts)

Replace with richer schema:
```typescript
ProTestAttempt {
  testId: ObjectId
  studentId: ObjectId
  startedAt: Date
  submittedAt: Date
  status: 'in_progress' | 'submitted'
  answers: [{
    questionId: string
    selectedOption: 'A'|'B'|'C'|'D' | null
  }]
  // Computed on submit
  totalMarks: number
  marksObtained: number
  negativeMarks: number
  correctCount: number
  wrongCount: number
  skippedCount: number
  percentage: number
  // Result details (stored after grading)
  gradedAnswers: [{
    questionId, questionText, studentAnswer, correctAnswer, reason, marksAwarded
  }]
  resultVisible: boolean  // mirrors test.resultMode at time of submit
}
```

---

### 2. Teacher Upload APIs

---

#### [MODIFY] [/api/admin/tests/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/tests/route.ts)

- [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/approve/route.ts#81-107) — list all tests (for teachers/admin), include attempt count
- [POST](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts#20-163) — accepts `multipart/form-data` with `questions` (File) + `answers` (File)
  1. Parse & validate `questions.json` — strict schema check
  2. Parse & validate `answers.json` — verify every `questionId` in answers exists in questions
  3. Save `ProTest` document
  4. Save `TestAnswerKey` document (separate collection)
  5. Return `{ success, testId, parsedQuestions, warnings }`

#### [MODIFY] [/api/admin/tests/[id]/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/tests/%5Bid%5D/route.ts)

- [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/approve/route.ts#81-107) — test detail + all attempts populated with student name
- [PATCH](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/attendance/route.ts#60-81) — toggle [isActive](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx#85-86), toggle result publishing (`isPublished = true`)
- [DELETE](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/tests/%5Bid%5D/route.ts#40-52) — cascade delete test + answer key + all attempts

#### [NEW] `/api/admin/tests/[id]/publish/route.ts`

- [PATCH](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/attendance/route.ts#60-81) — set `isPublished = true` and set `resultVisible = true` on all attempts for this test

---

### 3. Student APIs

---

#### [MODIFY] [/api/student/tests/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/tests/route.ts)

- [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/approve/route.ts#81-107) — return tests where `batch` matches student's batch AND `isActive = true`
- Strip correct answers, return only test meta + questions

#### [MODIFY] [/api/student/tests/[id]/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/tests/%5Bid%5D/route.ts)

- [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/approve/route.ts#81-107) — load test questions (no answers), check if already attempted
- [POST](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts#20-163) — submit answers:
  1. Check for duplicate attempt
  2. Load `TestAnswerKey` (server-only)
  3. Score: `marksObtained = (correct × marks) - (wrong × negativeMarking)`
  4. Build `gradedAnswers` array with reasons
  5. Save `ProTestAttempt`
  6. If `resultMode === 'instant'`, return full result + review
  7. If `resultMode === 'manual'`, return only `"Result will be published later"`

#### [MODIFY] [/api/student/tests/[id]/result/route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/tests/%5Bid%5D/result/route.ts)

- [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/approve/route.ts#81-107) — return attempt results if `resultVisible = true` OR `resultMode = 'instant'`
- Returns `gradedAnswers` including question text, student answer, correct answer, reason, marks

